                         Preamble

  The XPR Community Source License is a source-available,
community-oriented, and educational software license designed
to encourage learning, experimentation, technical curiosity,
and collaborative development while protecting creators from
unauthorized commercial exploitation.

  This license allows individuals, students, researchers,
developers, and communities to study, modify, and improve
software openly for non-commercial purposes. The intention of
this license is to support knowledge sharing and responsible
community-driven growth.

  Unlike traditional open-source licenses, this license does
not permit unrestricted commercial use. Commercial rights are
reserved exclusively for the original creator, owner, or
maintaining organization of the project using this License.

  These protections are intended to help creators share
their work openly with communities, students, researchers,
and developers without risking unauthorized commercial
exploitation of their efforts.

  Software development often requires significant time,
research, experimentation, maintenance, problem-solving,
creative effort, and long-term dedication. This License
exists to encourage healthy knowledge sharing while ensuring
that creators maintain fair control over how their work is
commercially used.

  The purpose of this License is not to discourage learning,
modification, or community contribution. Instead, it is
designed to support sustainable collaboration by preventing
situations where third parties commercially profit from the
work, reputation, or contributions of creators without
permission or meaningful participation.

